  "scout_brief": "Research how to make the algebraic variety in the central viewport update DYNAMICALLY/in real time as the user drags a parameter slider or moves the dot on the 2D/3D parameter grid. Today there is a deliberate buffer: the mesh re-renders only on slider-release / dot-release (interaction discipline INT-2; continuous re-render during drag is the INT-NO-1 anti-pattern) because the marching-cubes mesh generation is ~0.5s and would thrash the UI. The goal of this scout is a deep, ranked survey of optimization techniques that could shrink or hide that latency enough to make continuous update viable: pre-rendering / preloading / mesh caching keyed by parameter tuple, low-resolution coarse-preview during drag with full-res snap on release (level-of-detail), GPU-accelerated isosurfacing, background-thread / QThread mesh generation that respects the AI-9 _computing re-entrancy guard, parameter-space mesh interpolation or morphing between cached meshes, Numba/Cython JIT of the implicit-field evaluation, incremental / windowed marching cubes, adaptive sampling, and how peer scientific-viz tools achieve interactive parameter response. Hard constraints: AI-1 (PySide6+PyVista+VTK only), AI-3 (pv.OFF_SCREEN, never MainWindow offscreen), AI-9 (_computing re-entrancy guard), macOS Apple-Silicon-primary Qt+VTK GL offscreen constraint, single-developer cadence. Deliverable: a ranked candidate report of optimization approaches with effort/impact/risk.",
